UID:5319-1773493200-1773504000@bloomspinweave.org
SUMMARY:Intermediate Crochet With Lindsey Alumbaugh
DESCRIPTION:This workshop will walk you through how to make a Pacific Halibut Plush\, with pattern provided by the National Park Services! You will learn intermediate techniques such as treble crochet\, quadruple crochet\, DC2TOG\, and more!  \nSaturdays\, March 14 & 21\, 2026\, 1:00 – 4:00 PM \n$45 BSWG members \n$55 non-BSWG student members (includes one-year guild student membership) \n$75 non-BSWG members (includes one-year guild membership) \nClass size 2-10 students \nStudents must know basic crocheting.  \nThe instructor will provide all supplies or you may bring your own. Art Remains is a great option for sourcing supplies if you wish to bring your own.  \nREGISTRATION CLOSED \n\n           Download QR
URL:https://bloomspinweave.org/event/intermediate-crochet-with-lindsey-alumbaugh
LOCATION:Fiber Arts Center\, College Mall\, Bloomington\, 3038 East Third Street\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47401\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Fiber Arts Guild Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://bloomspinweave.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/intermediate-crochet.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Guild":MAILTO:educationbswg@gmail.com, newsletterbswg@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
